{
  "texts": [
    "To transform molecules into Functional Group(FG) graphs of a large dataset, Zewei Jiden et al.",
    "devised an algorithm for the automatic extraction of FGs from atom-level graphs, termed FG splitting in their work ReLMole 27.",
    "This method defines three types of substructures as building blocks for constructing FG-level graphs.",
    "Rings: For every ring structure within a molecule, it is designated as an FG.",
    "If two ring-form FGs share more than two atoms, implying the presence of bridge bonds between them, they are merged into a new FG."
  ]
}